OL,7,FMr Benn replied: "(Mr Burghart) did
OL,8,Fjust say that if this is the law, the
OL,9,Flaw needs to be changed, and I just
OL,10,Fwonder whether he is suggesting that
OL,11,Fthe arrangements for inquests, the way
OL,12,Fthey are conducted, coroner's sitting,
OL,13,Fhearing the evidence and coming to a
OL,14,Ffinding ` is he suggesting that that
OL,15,Fought to be changed?"
OL,17,FAfter nods from the Tory benches, Mr
OL,18,FBenn said: "Well, that's a very
OL,19,Finteresting observation from His
OL,20,FMajesty's Opposition."
