OL,7,FHe said: "I served in Northern
OL,8,FIreland, and some of the decisions you
OL,9,Fhad to take were instantaneous. You
OL,10,Fdidn't have time to mull them over.
OL,11,FThey were either life or death.
OL,13,F"I lost a very good friend, Captain
OL,14,FRobert Nairac, so the point that (Mr
OL,15,FBenn) makes when he says the trouble
OL,16,Fwith the last Legacy Act was that it
OL,17,Fgave immunity to IRA ` they have had
OL,18,Fimmunity, not just in letters of
OL,19,Fcomfort, but the fact they kept no
OL,20,Frecords, so they cannot be prosecuted.
OL,26,@oD@JOUuD@AOU
