OL,7,FMr Benn said he does "absolutely
OL,8,Funderstand and recognise the point he
OL,9,Fforcefully makes about the
OL,10,Fcircumstances in which our soldiers
OL,11,Ffound themselves as part of Operation
OL,12,FBanner".
OL,14,F"They'd seen their comrades killed.
OL,15,FThey don't know what they're going to
OL,16,Fface. These are very hard, and as he
OL,17,Frightly says, split-second decisions
OL,18,Fthe soldiers have to make in those
OL,19,Fcircumstances," he said.
